
OpenERP Client Library Guide
============================

First install the library: ::

    sudo easy_install openerp-client-lib

Now get inspired by the following script describing a simple interaction with an OpenERP server: ::

    import openerplib

    connection = openerplib.get_connection(hostname="localhost", database="my_db", \
        login="my_user", password="xxx")
    user_obj = connection.get_model("res.users")
    ids = user_obj.search([("login", "=", "admin")])
    user_info = user_obj.read(ids[0], ["name"])
    print user_info["name"]
    # will print "Administrator"


